MM benchmark comparison is clear: **auto-select and per-shape heuristic give nearly identical results** (~8.7 µs GM). Both are much better than the old no-split approach. The auto-select version is currently being submitted to leaderboard.

Key benchmark comparison:
| Shape | Auto-select | Per-shape | Old (no split, est.) |
|---|---|---|---|
| (16,2112,7168) | 17.2 µs | 17.3 µs | ~25+ µs |
| (64,7168,2048) | 9.62 µs | 9.73 µs | ~9.7 µs |
| (256,3072,1536) | 8.44 µs | 8.41 µs | ~8.4 µs |

The big win is on small-M/large-K shapes like (16,2112,7168) where splitK dramatically improves CU utilization. 

